comments: I found this class very helpful and learned a lot. I did not have any problems with the professor and thought the she graded fairly and treated everyone with respect and did not play favorites. i wish I would of taken her for com. 1

school_name: Eastern Florida State College - Palm Bay Campus
comments: The only thing I liked about this class was the literature we read. Ms. Rettich picks favorites from her old class and gives the "troublemakers" more freebies and privileges than the other students who actually try. Always late on grading and not understanding of student needs at all.

comments: she was clear and i learned alot from her class. hope i get her next semester for comm 2

school_name: Eastern Florida State College - Palm Bay Campus
comments: She has a extremely well personality and has a unique teaching ability. She doesn\'t have a mono tone and she can teach one on one if she has to. She puts in time for all the students and has even offered to help students after class if need be. she a little strict which is a good quality in a professor and she interacts with the class.

school_name: Eastern Florida State College - Palm Bay Campus
comments: very slow and repetitive. Extremely boring and not very helpful. This professor thinks your world revolves around her class. No make up for anything although, she is late with grading things herself. I would not take her again if possible.

school_name: Eastern Florida State College - Palm Bay Campus
comments: I took her class when I was in high school. When I saw she was teaching English in college as well, I immediately signed up. She\'s a really respectful woman, awesome awesome. The only downside to it was that I felt like I was in high school again. And if you know anything about English, I\'d say she\'s very easy. Unless you want a challenge.
